{
  "$comment": [
    "Static operation counts for one evaluation of each variant, read off the GLSL",
    "sources by hand. This is the analytical half of the cost model; the measured",
    "half lives in the benchmark. Counting them separately means neither has to be",
    "trusted alone: the op counts have no measurement noise but cannot know what a",
    "particular GPU charges for a transcendental, and the timings know exactly that",
    "but wobble by a few percent.",
    "",
    "Fields: l = lowbias32 calls (the hash primitive; hash2u is 2, hash3u is 3),",
    "t = sin/cos, a = atan, q = sqrt, e = exp, alu = everything else, roughly.",
    "Loops are counted fully unrolled: a 3x3 neighbourhood is 9 iterations, 3x3x3",
    "is 27.",
    "",
    "Weights below are relative instruction costs on a typical GPU: integer",
    "multiply chains and transcendentals cost several times a plain ALU op."
  ],
  "weights": {
    "l": 6,
    "t": 8,
    "a": 16,
    "q": 4,
    "e": 8,
    "alu": 1
  },
